The paper discusses testing strategies for Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithms, which are commonly used in probabilistic modeling and inference. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), systems and control (cs.SY), and modeling and simulation (cs.MS). However, given the focus on probabilistic modeling and inference, as well as the use of a specific example involving a mixture of Gaussians model, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
